{
  "doc_id": "37702",
  "text": "Mitochondria or mitochondria-like organelles are part of the essential inventory of eukaryotic cells. Their origin can be traced down to an endosymbiotic event between what were probably two prokaryotic organisms: a host cell of uncertain lineage and an intracellular symbiont with the characteristic features of an a proteobacterium [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
